# Superpowers Dependencies for Gemini CLI

While Superpowers is primarily a collection of behavioral skills, some features require external tools to be available in the environment where Gemini CLI is running.

## Core Requirements
- Git: Required for using-git-worktrees and finishing-a-development-branch.
- Standard UNIX Tools: grep, find, sed, ls are used by various debugging and exploration skills.

## Optional Requirements
- Node.js (v18+): Required for the writing-skills tool if you wish to use the render-graphs.js utility.
- Bash/Zsh: Required for running the systematic-debugging helper scripts.

## Project-Specific Dependencies
Skills like test-driven-development and verification-before-completion will attempt to run your project's native commands (e.g., npm test, pytest, make, etc.). Ensure your local project environment is correctly set up.
